<h4>{{ _('LED Strip Configuration') }}</h4>

<br />
<p>GPIO pins should be specified as <a href="http://elinux.org/RPi_Low-level_peripherals#General_Purpose_Input.2FOutput_.28GPIO.29">physical pin numbers</a>, not GPIO/BCM numbers.</p>
<br />

<form class="form-horizontal">
    <div class="control-group">
        <label class="control-label">Red Pin Number</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <input type="number" step="any" min="0" class="input-mini text-right" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.LEDStripControl.r">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="control-group">
        <label class="control-label">Green Pin Number</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <input type="number" step="any" min="0" class="input-mini text-right" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.LEDStripControl.g">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="control-group">
        <label class="control-label">Blue Pin Number</label>
        <div class="controls">
            <input type="number" step="any" min="0" class="input-mini text-right" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.LEDStripControl.b">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="control-group">
        <label class="checkbox">
            <input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.LEDStripControl.piblaster">Use <a href="https://github.com/sarfata/pi-blaster">Pi-Blaster</a>
            <span class="help-inline">If unchecked use RPi.GPIO.  Pi-Blaster should give smoother PWM frequencies but requires a more involved setup.</span>
        </label>
    </div>
</form>
